To add a button with text "Good", you can use HTML and CSS code. Here's an example:

```html
<button class="good-button">Good</button>
```

And then style it using CSS:

```css
.good-button {
  background-color: green;
  color: white;
  font-size: 18px;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
  cursor: pointer;
}
```

This will create a green button with white text that says "Good". The button will have a border-radius of 5px, which gives it rounded corners, and a cursor of "pointer" to indicate that it is clickable. You can modify the CSS to customize the button further to your liking.
